               <ce:legend>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0060" view="all">For location, * indicates similar sampling of only dominant or co-dominant trees within 1 km of each other. For forest type, P = primary, S = secondary. P * indicates partially logged primary forest with one tree regenerating after logging. P^ indicates former primary forest. S* indicates at least one veteran tree. Dead trees among samples noted by °. Crossdating statistics are for all rings sampled per location. Missing rings (MR) determined by crossdating and exclude undated inner rings (not bound sections). Tree-level chronologies generated using series ≥ 30 yr with high crossdating confidence and detrended with 32-yr spline. Standard versions are combined into location chronologies with no further detrending. For length, ^ indicates gap in chronology: 2 (1605–1639, 1672–1701), 15 A (1392–1500, 1715–1765, 1914–1959), 18 (1019–1289), 20 (1112–1115). Two-tree cutoff is earliest year with two-tree replication. R-bar is mean correlation between pairs of trees per location. MR for chronologies only include constituent series.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:legend>
