               <ce:legend>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0070" view="all">For forest type, P = primary, S = secondary. Veteran trees are in or near secondary forests. P^ indicates deadwood remnant from primary forests. Mixed crown classes denote sampling dominant (Dom.) and co-dominant (Co.) to subordinate trees. Completely-sampled trees (*) have replicate cores at BH, TB, and 10-m increments and are one of at least four trees located within 1 km of each other. Missing rings are determined by crossdating and exclude undated inner rings (not bound). For crossdating categories, mean is above and range is below in parentheses. Crossdating categories do not show unusable rings due to decay or lost pieces of core.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:legend>
            </ce:table>
            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" id="tbl0020" colsep="0" rowsep="0" frame="topbot">
               <ce:label>Table 4</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0060">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0075" view="all">Summary of nonparametric regression models predicting tree-level crossdating metrics for <ce:italic>Sequoia</ce:italic> in primary forests.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0060" role="short">Table 4</ce:alt-text>
               <tgroup cols="7">
                  <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
                  <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
                  <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3"/>
                  <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4"/>
                  <colspec colnum="5" colname="col5"/>
                  <colspec colnum="6" colname="col6"/>
                  <colspec colnum="7" colname="col7"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Response variable</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Predictors</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Trees</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">
                           <italic>N</italic>*</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">x<italic>R</italic>
                           <sup loc="post">2</sup>
                        </entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">x<italic>R</italic>
                           <sup loc="post">2</sup> change</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Sensitivity</entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" role="rowhead">Undated rings (%)</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">
                           <bold>Age</bold>, DTB</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">122</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">52</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">0.40</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">0.32, 0.08</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">
                           <bold>0.49</bold>, 0.18</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" role="rowhead">Missing rings (%)</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">
                           <bold>Age</bold>, Latitude, Heartwood volume</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">122</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">15</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">0.57</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">0.41, 0.09, 0.07</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">
                           <bold>0.86</bold>, 0.57, 0.32</entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
               <ce:legend>
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0080" view="all">Average neighborhood size (N * ) is amount of data bearing on response estimate per point. Predictors are tree age (yr), trunk diameter at top of buttress (DTB, cm), latitude (°), and trunk heartwood volume (m3). Sensitivity is mean absolute difference resulting from nudging predictor (delta = 0.05) expressed as proportion of dependent variable’s range. Cross-validated correlation (xR2) is computed as 1 – (residual sum of squares / total sum of squares) and based on leave-one-out cross validation. Strongest predictor (highest sensitivity) is highlighted bold, and xR2 change indicates dependence of final model on number of predictors.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:legend>
            </ce:table>
            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" id="tbl0025" colsep="0" rowsep="0" frame="topbot">
               <ce:label>Table 5</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0065">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0085" view="all">Summary of Friedman's nonparametric rank sum test for differences in crossdating metrics across sample heights for <ce:italic>Sequoia</ce:italic> in primary forests.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
               <ce:alt-text id="at0065" role="short">Table 5</ce:alt-text>
               <tgroup cols="6">
                  <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1"/>
                  <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2"/>
                  <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3"/>
                  <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4"/>
                  <colspec colnum="5" colname="col5"/>
                  <colspec colnum="6" colname="col6"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row rowsep="1">
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Dependent variable</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Trees</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Duration (yr)</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">Source of variation</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">DF</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">χ<sup loc="post">2</sup>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                     <row>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd" role="rowhead">Undated rings (%)</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">46</entry>
                        <entry xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/dtd">345 (69–969)</entry>
